sql:
SELECT DISTINCT callsign
FROM repeaters
WHERE area_id = 1;

SELECT users.user_name, users.email
FROM users
INNER JOIN repeater_comments ON users.user_id = repeater_comments.user_id;

SELECT DISTINCT users.user_name, users.email
FROM users
JOIN repeater_comments ON users.user_id = repeater_comments.user_id;

SELECT repeater_id, callsign
FROM repeaters
WHERE repeater_type = 'digital' AND status_id = 1;

SELECT COUNT(*) AS 'TR72 Digital Repeater Count' 
FROM repeaters 
WHERE repeater_model = 'TR72' AND repeater_type = 'digital';

SELECT roles.role_name, user_permissions.permission_name
FROM roles
JOIN user_permissions ON roles.role_id = user_permissions.role_id;

external_knowledge:
- 'unique beacons' refers to repeater IDs;
- 'sailing smoothly under a clear sky' metaphorically means repeaters with a status ID of 1, indicating a positive operational status;
- 'the name of their current voyage status' refers to the status name associated with the repeater's operational status.

- 'Listening capability' refers to the highest receive frequency (rx_freq) of the repeaters;
- The model of the repeater gives insight into its specific design and features;
- The transmission detail relates to the transmit frequency (tx_freq);
- The operational status indicates whether the repeater is active, under maintenance, or decommissioned;
- The region denotes the province or state (pr_st_id) where the repeater is located.

sql:
SELECT repeater_model, tx_freq, location_id, status_id, pr_st_id
FROM repeaters
WHERE rx_freq = (SELECT MAX(rx_freq) FROM repeaters);

external_knowledge:
- Frequent maintenance refers to repeaters that have undergone more than ten maintenance services. ;
- The repeater IDs with higher maintenance counts are listed first. ;
- A higher maintenance frequency might indicate issues with the repeater's reliability or operational conditions.

sql:
SELECT * 
FROM repeaters 
JOIN locations ON repeaters.location_id = locations.location_id;

SELECT r.callsign, l.location_name
FROM repeaters r
JOIN locations l ON r.location_id = l.location_id;

SELECT callsign, tx_freq 
FROM repeaters 
WHERE tx_freq = (SELECT MAX(tx_freq) FROM repeaters);

external_knowledge:
'last month of summer' refers to August 2022; 'tune-up' refers to maintenance activities.;
'their sites' refers to the locations of the repeaters.;
'regions they're in' refers to the provinces or states where the repeaters are located.

- "stewards of the digital garden" refers to the users;
- "roles" are the responsibilities or positions they hold;
- "seeds they planted" metaphorically represents the types of activities they performed;
- "whispers they shared" refers to the comments they made;
- "the last day of the year 2022" indicates December 31, 2022.

